Clean the mushrooms with a cloth or brush (do not wash them or the flavour disappears).Roughly chop any large mushrooms and leave the smaller ones intact.Put the water, lemon juice and some salt into a saucepan.Bring to the boil and add the mushrooms.Simmer for approximately four minutes.Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the olive oil, garlic, parsley and olives.Drain the mushrooms and add immediately to the olive oil marinade.Mix well, check for seasoning and leave to cool.Serve with lemon wedges.